## Step 1: Prerequisites
 
### Generate a service token
To generate a service token:
1. In your dbt Cloud account, go to **Account Settings**.

2. Go to **Service Tokens** and click **+ New Token** to generate a new service token.

3. Copy the token and paste it in a safe place.
 
:::caution
 
Your new token will not be displayed again, so make sure to save it in a safe place.
 
:::
 
## Step 2: Set up the dbt Cloud integration in Airbyte Cloud

To set up the dbt Cloud integration in Airbyte Cloud:
1. On the Airbyte Cloud dashboard, click **Settings** in the navigation bar.

2. In the **Workspace settings** sidebar, click **dbt Cloud integration**.

3. Paste the [Service Token](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/dbt-cloud-apis/service-tokens) from [Step 1](#generate-a-service-token) and click **Save changes**.

4. Click **Connections** in the navigation bar and select the connection you want to add a dbt job to.

5. Go to the **Transformation** tab and click **+ Add transformation**.

6. Select a transformation from the dropdown and save the changes.
 
## Optional: Display the dbt Cloud integration logs

To display the dbt Cloud integration logs:
1. Go to the **Status** tab of the connection and click **Sync now**.

2. After the connection syncs, click on the destination.
 
   Run History is displayed.
 
3. Click on a job in the Run History list.

4. In the **Run Steps** section, click the **Invoke `dbt run`** dropdown.

5. You can select either **Console Logs** or **Debug Logs** to display them.
